.TH "i40e_ptp_gettimex" 9 "i40e_ptp_gettimex" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i40e_ptp_gettimex \- Get the time of the PHC
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i40e_ptp_gettimex
.BI "(struct ptp_clock_info *ptp "  ","
.BI "struct timespec64 *ts "  ","
.BI "struct ptp_system_timestamp *sts "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ptp" 12
The PTP clock structure
.IP "ts" 12
timespec structure to hold the current time value
.IP "sts" 12
structure to hold the system time before and after reading the PHC
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Read the device clock and return the correct value on ns, after converting it
into a timespec struct.
